Summary of Amendments Adopted by House
The Committee Amendments Proposed by House Committee on Retirement to the
original bill:
1. Remove proposed provision concerning term limits.
2. Provide that active members of the board of trustees are elected by active
members of the system.
3. Provide that three members elected are members of the Professional Fire Fighters
Association and two members are elected by nonmembers of the Professional
Fire Fighters Association.
4. Remove proposed provisions authorizing the board of trustees to fill a vacancy
by appointment with less than two years left of the term.
5. Add provisions repealing present law appointment of fire chiefs to the board of
trustees by the La. Fire Chiefs Association.
6. Provide that upon the effective date of proposed law, the terms of certain
members serving on the board terminate; however, such members remain on the
board of trustees until members are elected as provided in proposed law.
7. Provide that proposed law is effective upon signature of governor or lapse of
time for gubernatorial action.
8. Make technical changes.
